00:00:02.419 --> 00:00:05.620
Take a Picture with the HTC Inspire 4G ™ PD98120
Welcome to AT&amp;T “How To” videos.

00:00:05.620 --> 00:00:11.580
Today we will show you how to Take a Picture
with the HTC Inspire 4G ™

00:00:11.580 --> 00:00:14.590
First we will show you how to take a picture.

00:00:14.590 --> 00:00:20.190
To begin, from the Home screen, tap Camera.
The camera viewfinder will be displayed on

00:00:20.190 --> 00:00:25.840
the screen. Then aim the camera, and then
make the desired adjustments:

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:31.220
Zoom: Slide up or down on the left side of
the screen to zoom in our out.

00:00:31.220 --> 00:00:36.489
Please Note: Alternatively, users can zoom
in and out with the Volume key.

00:00:36.489 --> 00:00:41.870
Focus: Tap on the desired portion of the screen
to adjust the focus.

00:00:41.870 --> 00:00:46.710
Please Note: The viewfinder will auto focus
after accessing the camera, moving the lens,

00:00:46.710 --> 00:00:52.829
or adjusting the focus.
Flash: Then tap the flash icon to adjust the

00:00:52.829 --> 00:00:58.769
camera flash setting.
Effects: Then tap the effects icon to add

00:00:58.769 --> 00:01:03.519
an image effect.
Flick to and tap the desired effect to enable

00:01:03.519 --> 00:01:08.619
it.
Next tap the shutter icon to take a picture.

00:01:08.619 --> 00:01:13.340
Here a preview of your picture will be displayed.

00:01:13.340 --> 00:01:16.310
Next we will show you how to adjust the camera
settings.

00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:22.260
To begin, from the Home screen, tap Camera.
Press the Menu key, and then adjust the settings

00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:26.710
as desired:
Self-portrait: This enables self-portrait

00:01:26.710 --> 00:01:29.939
mode to automatically focus and take your
picture.

00:01:29.939 --> 00:01:35.179
Self-timer: Lets you insert a delay between
when you tap the shutter and when the photo

00:01:35.179 --> 00:01:40.340
is taken.
Image adjustments: This sets the exposure,

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:47.649
contrast, saturation and sharpness levels.
White balance: This sets the lighting conditions

00:01:47.649 --> 00:01:54.960
preset.
Resolution: This lets you set the ISO sensitivity.

00:01:54.960 --> 00:02:01.759
ISO: This sets the ISO sensitivity.
Review duration: This sets the length of time

00:02:01.759 --> 00:02:08.720
the preview is displayed after taking a photo.
Widescreen: This enables the widescreen photos.

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:19.120
Geo-tag photos: This enables geotagging.
Auto focus: This enables auto focus.

00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:25.739
Face detection: This enables face detection.
Shutter sound: This enables the shutter noise

00:02:25.739 --> 00:02:33.150
when taking a photo.
Grid: Displays: a grid over the viewfinder.

00:02:33.150 --> 00:02:38.250
Reset to default: Tap to return to the default
settings.

00:02:38.250 --> 00:02:45.040
If further assistance is needed feel free
to contact our online Business Support Team

00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:50.440
at www.att.com/biztech. If accessing the site
for the first time you will need to enter

00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:53.790
your device model and click "Next".

00:02:53.790 --> 00:02:55.950
Thank you for choosing AT&amp;T.

